cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY

The paper discusses Spectre and Meltdown attacks, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and involve micro-architectural side-channels (cs.AR). The paper also explores the implications of these attacks for programming languages (cs.PL) and discusses the need for mitigations (cs.SE) and understanding of speculative vulnerabilities (cs.SY). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
